OL,3,CThe Cammell Laird 37: Jailed strikers
OL,4,Cfight to clear their names
OL,6,FThe current Cammell Laird shipyard is
OL,7,Fstill a household name, but is an
OL,8,Fentirely different company to the one
OL,9,Fthat was the centre of an industrial
OL,10,Frow in the 1980s - eventually
OL,11,Fprivatised by Margaret Thatcher's
OL,12,Fgovernment.
OL,14,FBy 1984, deindustrialisation had
OL,15,Fchanged the working landscape, and by
OL,16,FMay 1,000 compulsory redundancies had
OL,17,Fbeen announced.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/13
