OL,3,CThe Cammell Laird 37: Jailed strikers
OL,4,Cfight to clear their names
OL,6,F"We were away from our homes, living
OL,7,Fon the rig, with no beds, no proper
OL,8,Ffurniture, the only thing that kept us
OL,9,Fgoing - and I think this has a lot to
OL,10,Fdo with us being Scousers - was we
OL,11,Ftook the mickey out of each other, we
OL,12,Fwere a very tight knit group.
OL,14,F"We believed in each other, so we
OL,15,Fthought that if we stuck together,
OL,16,Fwe'd win."
OL,18,FWhy were they jailed?
OL,20,FThe occupation eventually ended when
OL,21,Fthe water supplies were cut off.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/13
