OL,3,CThe Cammell Laird 37: Jailed strikers
OL,4,Cfight to clear their names
OL,6,FThe 37 were jailed at HMP Walton for
OL,7,Fone month on the charge of contempt of
OL,8,Fcourt for refusing to abandon their
OL,9,Foccupation and attend legal
OL,10,Fproceedings initiated by management.
OL,12,F"We thought it was scandalous - you're
OL,13,Fordinary men fighting for our jobs,
OL,14,Fand the next thing you have a prison
OL,15,Funiform on, and you're walking around
OL,16,Fa prison yard!" Billy remembers.
OL,18,F"Some men took it harder than others.
OL,19,FThere were some who were crying
OL,20,Fbecause they were away from their
OL,21,Ffamilies."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/13
