OL,3,CThe Cammell Laird 37: Jailed strikers
OL,4,Cfight to clear their names
OL,6,F"It stuck in everyone's memory. I
OL,7,Factually went with other men for jobs,
OL,8,Fand I always got knocked back.
OL,10,F"We got it really bad. If it wasn't
OL,11,Ffor some of the collections and the
OL,12,Fcity council giving us food baskets,
OL,13,Fthen we would have really been
OL,14,Fstruggling. We struggled a lot."
OL,16,FWhat's happening now?
OL,18,FNow aged in their 70s and 80s, the
OL,19,FCammell Laird 37 remain the largest
OL,20,Fgroup in Britain to be jailed for
OL,21,Funion action.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/13
