OL,3,CThe Cammell Laird 37: Jailed strikers
OL,4,Cfight to clear their names
OL,6,F"We would like a minister to meet with
OL,7,Fthe campaigners and the legal team to
OL,8,Fhear what help they need to exonerate
OL,9,Ftheir names. We would like a concrete
OL,10,Fcommitment to searching for and
OL,11,Freleasing every last document that
OL,12,Frelates to this case.
OL,14,F"We need answers as to who was behind
OL,15,Fthe instructions that ensured that 37
OL,16,Fhard-working people were put in jail
OL,17,Ffor contempt of court, just for
OL,18,Ffighting for their employment, for
OL,19,Ftheir right to work to put food on the
OL,20,Ftable and to clothe their children.
OL,21,FThese men had committed no crime."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G12/13
